The highest-leverage low-overhead change is a fixed 15-minute weekly manager check-in that replaces status-heavy 1:1 time, not adds to it. Use the same three questions every week: what is frustrating you, where are you stuck, and what would make next week better; end with one action item, and review repeated themes monthly. That catches flight-risk signals early, shows follow-through, and creates almost no extra management load.
